<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880816-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Southland Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NCS VESP </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Southland Corp., Dallas, said it completed the purchase of 43 convenience stores in Las Vegas, Nev., from National Convenience Stores Inc. of Houston.    Terms weren't disclosed. Both companies own and operate convenience stores.    Separately, Southland said it completed the sale of its snack foods division to Vesper Corp. for an undisclosed price. As previously reported, Southland has been selling assets to pay down debt incurred in its $4.9 billion leveraged buyout last year.    The company said it has repaid $833 million in debt to date, putting it more than a year ahead of schedule. </TEXT></DOC>